						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the Tripurasundarī-ammaṉ shrine in the Vēdapurīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājēndradēva (II): Year 11 = 1061-62 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription commences with <hi rend="italic">Iraṭṭapāḍi ēḻarai ilakkamum,</hi> etc. and mentions the <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhmaṇa</hi> Gautamaṉ of <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> Tiruvāṉmiyūr in Kōṭṭūr-nāḍu in Puliyūr-kkōṭṭam in Jayaṅgoṇḍaśōḻa-maṇḍalam.</p>						

